'''''L'Encha<U+00EE>n<U+00E9> du Nord et du Pas-de-Calais''''' was a [[French Communist Party|Communist Party]] weekly newspaper published from [[Lille]], [[France]], published on Fridays.<ref name="p2">''[http://books.google.com/books?id=IlnQAAAAMAAJ Nomenclature des journaux & revues en langue fran<U+00E7>aise du monde entier]''. Paris, Les bureaux de l'Argus, 1937. p. 360</ref><ref>Schor, Ralph. ''[http://books.google.com/books?id=ikuRSkH_AO4C&pg=PA L'opinion fran<U+00E7>aise et les <U+00E9>trangers en France, 1919-1939]''. [Paris]: Publication de la Sorbonne, 1985. pp. 18, 575</ref><ref>Christophe, Paul. ''[http://books.google.com/books?id=2AT0UdtmI_MC&pg=PA146 1936: les catholiques et le Front populaire]''. Paris: Editions ouvri<U+00E8>res, 1986. p. 146</ref> St<U+00EA>phane Dubled was the editor-in-chief of ''l'Encha<U+00EE>n<U+00E9>''.<ref name="p2"/>

The first issue of ''l'Encha<U+00EE>n<U+00E9>'' was published on May 26, 1923. It replaced a previous Lille-based communist publication, ''Le Prol<U+00E9>taire''. The founding director of the new publication was Guy Jerram, secretary of the Nord federation of the Communist Party. Moreover the editorial and administrative staff of ''Le Prol<U+00E9>taire'' passed on to ''l'Encha<U+00EE>n<U+00E9>''.<ref>Visse, Jean-Paul. ''[http://books.google.com/books?id=oulEUWg3AdYC&pg=PA219 La presse du Nord et du Pas-de-Calais au temps de l'<U+00C9>cho du Nord: 1819-1944]''. Villeneuve d'Ascq: Presses Univ. du Septentrion, 2004. pp. 219-220</ref> At the time the [[Second World War]] broke out, ''l'Encha<U+00EE>n<U+00E9>'' had a circulation of around 100,000.<ref>Visse, Jean-Paul. ''[http://books.google.com/books?id=oulEUWg3AdYC&pg=PA233 La presse du Nord et du Pas-de-Calais au temps de l'<U+00C9>cho du Nord: 1819-1944]''. Villeneuve d'Ascq: Presses Univ. du Septentrion, 2004. p. 233</ref>

